The paper deals with a novel group testing method that has applications in genome screening experiments. The paper proposes a unifying framework for group testing, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also describes several combinatorial and probabilistic constructions for codes, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The paper also describes decoding algorithms and a belief propagation decoder, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
